dnorshire, Wales":"Presteigne, Radnorshire, Wales, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"ABT 1174–":"omkring 1174–Afdød","1174–Male":"1174–Afdød","1185–Female":"1185–Afdød","1210–1243":"1210–1243","–Male":"Afdød","1160–Male":"1160–Afdød","1160–Female":"1160–Afdød","ABT 1174":"omkring 1174","ABT 1210":"omkring 1210","1243":"1243","1210":"1210","1185":"1185","1174":"1174","1160":"1160","Presteigne, Radnor,, Wales":"Presteigne, Radnorshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Presteigne, Llythyfnwg, Radnorshire, Wales":"Presteigne, Radnorshire, Wales, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"ABT 1174–":"circa 1174–Overleden","1174–Male":"1174–Overleden","1185–Female":"1185–Overleden","1210–1243":"1210–1243","–Male":"Overleden","1160–Male":"1160–Overleden","1160–Female":"1160–Overleden","ABT 1174":"circa 1174","ABT 1210":"circa 1210","1243":"1243","1210":"1210","1185":"1185","1174":"1174","1160":"1160","Presteigne, Radnor,, Wales":"Presteigne, Radnorshire, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Presteigne, Llythyfnwg, Radnorshire, Wales":"Presteigne, Radnorshire, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England, United Kingdom":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"ABT 1174–":"about 1174–Deceased","1174–Male":"1174–Deceased","1185–Female":"1185–Deceased","1210–1243":"1210–1243","–Male":"Deceased","1160–Male":"1160–Deceased","1160–Female":"1160–Deceased","ABT 1174":"about 1174","ABT 1210":"about 1210","1243":"1243","1210":"1210","1185":"1185","1174":"1174","1160":"1160","Presteigne, Radnor,, Wales":"Presteigne, Radnorshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Presteigne, Llythyfnwg, Radnorshire, Wales":"Presteigne, Radnorshire, Wales, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"ap","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Abt  .","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): habitational name from Apt, the Yiddish name of Opatów in Świętokrzyskie Voivodeship, Poland. The placename (in German, Yiddish, and Polish) is from a root meaning ‘abbot’, the place having been named for the local abbey. Compare   Abt  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Abt","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Helmut, Horst, Johann, Kurt.","German and Dutch: from Middle Low German or Middle Dutch <i>abt</i> ‘abbot’, hence a metonymic occupational name for a servant of an abbot or a nickname for someone thought to resemble an abbot in some way. In some instances it may have been a topographic or habitational name referring to a house named with this word.","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): variant of   Abt  , a habitational name from Opatów in Poland."]},{"name":"Apter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Avrohom, Bronya, Eliezer, Naftali.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Apt (see   Apt  ).","English: habitational name from Aptor in Marldon, Devon, composed of Old English <i>uppe</i> ‘up, above’ + <i>torr</i> ‘rocky outcrop’."]}]},{"name":"Mredydd","type":"LAST","meanings":["This is said to be the same name as Meriadek or Meiradwg, and also as the] Irish name O'Muireadwg, and the Scotch Mac Muireadaigh and Muir- eadhach. O'Reilly, however, renders the Irish word muireadach 'a sovereign, a lord j also a man's name, Morogh.' It means rather l admiral,' literally protector of the sea; from muir the sea, eadhach protector. I derive the British name from mawreddwg, mawreddig, magnificent, great, from mawr, great."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Vychan","type":"LAST","meanings":["Welsh: A Welsh name of great antiquity, from vyckan, little, small; i.e. small in stature. Compare the surname Bychan and the Armoric Le Bihan."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Llewelyn","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional: altered form (influenced by <i>llew</i> ‘lion’) of <i>Llywelyn</i>, an ancient name of uncertain derivation. It probably goes back to the Old Celtic name <i>Lugobelinos</i>, the first element of which is <i>Lugu-</i> (the name of a god;  see  Lleu  ); the second is a name-forming element found also in names such as <i>Cunobelinus</i> (<i>Cymbeline</i>). The name was borne by  Llywelyn ap Iorwerth  (  1173–1240 ) and his grandson Llywelyn ap Gruffydd (  d. 1282 ), Welsh princes who for a time united their countrymen in North Wales and led opposition to the power of the Norman barons in South Wales and the Marches."],"variants":[{"name":"Llywellyn","meanings":["Traditional: altered form (influenced by <i>llew</i> ‘lion’) of <i>Llywelyn</i>, an ancient name of uncertain derivation. It probably goes back to the Old Celtic name <i>Lugobelinos</i>, the first element of which is <i>Lugu-</i> (the name of a god;  see  Lleu  ); the second is a name-forming element found also in names such as <i>Cunobelinus</i> (<i>Cymbeline</i>). The name was borne by  Llywelyn ap Iorwerth  (  1173–1240 ) and his grandson Llywelyn ap Gruffydd (  d. 1282 ), Welsh princes who for a time united their countrymen in North Wales and led opposition to the power of the Norman barons in South Wales and the Marches."]},{"name":"Llywelyn","meanings":["(Welsh)  See  Llewelyn ."]},{"name":"Llewellyn","meanings":["Traditional: altered form (influenced by <i>llew</i> ‘lion’) of <i>Llywelyn</i>, an ancient name of uncertain derivation. It probably goes back to the Old Celtic name <i>Lugobelinos</i>, the first element of which is <i>Lugu-</i> (the name of a god;  see  Lleu  ); the second is a name-forming element found also in names such as <i>Cunobelinus</i> (<i>Cymbeline</i>). The name was borne by  Llywelyn ap Iorwerth  (  1173–1240 ) and his grandson Llywelyn ap Gruffydd (  d. 1282 ), Welsh princes who for a time united their countrymen in North Wales and led opposition to the power of the Norman barons in South Wales and the Marches."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Llewelyn ap Mredydd Vychan was born abou